quran[5]{c,v,t,f}:
33,31,"But whoever of you is obedient to Allah and His Messenger and does good deeds, Allah will double her reward. {1} We have prepared for her a generous provision.",footnotes:1:The reason for giving a double punishment for a sin and a double reward for a good work is that those whom Allah honors with a high rank in society generally become the leaders of men and the majority of the people follow them for good or for evil. Thus
33,32,"Wives of the Prophet, you are not like other women. {1} If you fear Allah, do not be too complaisant in your speech lest those with diseased hearts should covet you; but speak in a straight forward manner. {2}",footnotes:1:As for the sentence
33,33,"And stay in your homes {1} and do not go about displaying your allurements as in the former Time of Ignorance. {2} Establish Prayer, give Zakah, and obey Allah and His Messenger. Allah only wishes to remove uncleanness from you, O members of the (Prophet's) household, and to purify you completely. {3}",footnotes:1:In the presence of such a clear and express command of the Quran
33,34,"Remember the Signs of Allah and the words of wisdom which are rehearsed in your homes. {1} Verily Allah is All-Subtle, {2} All-Aware.",footnotes:1:The word wadhkurna in the original has two meanings: Remember and mention. According to the first meaning the verse would mean: “O wives of the Prophet (peace be upon him)
33,35,"Surely {1} the men who submit (to Allah) and the women who submit (to Allah), {2} the men who have faith and the women who have faith, {3} the men who are obedient and the women who are obedient, {4} the men who are truthful and the women who are truthful; {5} the men who are steadfast and the women who are steadfast, {6} the men who humble themselves (to Allah) and the women who humble themselves (to Allah), {7} the men who give alms and the women who give alms, {8} the men who fast and the women who fast, {9} the men who guard their chastity and the women who guard their chastity, {10} the men who remember Allah much and the women who remember Allah much: {11} for them has Allah prepared forgiveness and a mighty reward. {12}",footnotes:1:Presentation of this theme immediately after the foregoing paragraph contains a subtle allusion to the fact that the instructions given above to the Prophet’s (peace be upon him) wives are not exclusively meant for them but the Muslim society as a whole should reform itself in accordance with them.|180412:Who have surrendered themselves to Allah: Who have accepted Islam as a code of life for themselves
